 12  /-- An encodable type is a "constructively countable" type. This is where
 13    we have an explicit injection `encode : α → nat` and a partial inverse
 14    `decode : nat → option α`. This makes the range of `encode` decidable,
 15    although it is not decidable if `α` is finite or not. -/
 16  class encodable (α : Type*) :=
id                        └───┘
typ                       └───┘
 17  (encode : α → nat) (decode : nat → option α) (encodek : ∀ a, decode (encode a) = some a)
id             ┴ ┴ └─┘            └─┘ ┴ └────┘ ┴               ┴  └────┘  └────┘ ┴  ┴ └──┘ ┴
src                └─┘            └─┘   └────┘                                      ┴ └──┘
typ            ┴ ┴ └─┘            └─┘ ┴ └────┘ ┴               ┴  └────┘  └────┘ ┴  ┴ └──┘ ┴
